	Karate Combat (KC) is a brand which promotes the first professional
	full-contact karate league, hosting worldwide events since April 2018. The
	private company is headquartered in New York and was founded by Michael
	DePietro and Robert Bryan. The brand also encompasses sports equipment, a
	worldwide Dojo network and mobile apps for viewers. Karate Combat was
	founded in order to promote karate as a sport and martial art. Former UFC
	heavyweight champion Bas Rutten hosts Karate Combat venues alongside special
	guests.
